				\begin{document}$$\delta^{13} C \, or \, \delta^{15} N \, \left( \permille \right) \, = \, \left( {R_{{{\text{sample}}}} /R_{{{\text{standard}}}} - 1} \right) \, \times \, 1000 \, \left( {R \, =^{13} C/^{12} C,^{15} N/^{14} N} \right)$$\end{document}δ13Corδ15N‱=Rsample/Rstandard-1×1000R=13C/12C,15N/14Nwhere Rsample is the abundance ratio of the sample, Rstandard is the international standard, Vienna Pee Dee Belemnite, and atmospheric nitrogen. The analytical errors for the isotope analysis were within 0.1‰ for δ13C and 0.2‰ for δ15N.
